cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a machine learning model for speech detection, which involves signal processing, natural language processing, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The model also involves optimization and sparsity constraints, which are related to cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
